sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant LS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Garak as Garak Subprocess<br/>(NVIDIA Garak 0.12.0)
    participant Shield as SimpleShieldOrchestrator<br/>httpx HTTP/2
    participant Safety as Safety API<br/>8321/TCP loopback
    participant vLLM as vLLM Endpoint<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Files as Files API<br/>(in-process)
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Inline Garak Scan (Local Execution)
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    LS->>Garak: Launch subprocess<br/>(semaphore-controlled)
    Garak->>vLLM: Red-team probes<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, API Token
    vLLM-->>Garak: Model responses
    Garak-->>LS: Scan results (JSON, HTML, logs)
    LS->>Files: Store reports<br/>(in-process)
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/eval/jobs/result<br/>8321/TCP
    LS-->>Client: Scan results (0.0-1.0 score)
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/openai/v1/files/{id}/content<br/>8321/TCP
    LS-->>Client: Download reports

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Inline Scan with Shield Testing
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run (with shields)<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    LS->>Garak: Launch subprocess<br/>(function.Single mode)
    Garak->>Shield: Probe with shield config
    Shield->>Safety: POST /safety/run-shield<br/>8321/TCP loopback
    Safety-->>Shield: Shield check result
    Shield->>LS: POST /openai/v1/chat/completions<br/>8321/TCP loopback
    LS->>vLLM: Forward inference<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    vLLM-->>LS: Model response
    LS-->>Shield: Inference result
    Shield->>Safety: POST /safety/run-shield (output)<br/>8321/TCP loopback
    Safety-->>Shield: Output shield result
    Shield-->>Garak: Orchestrated response
    Garak-->>LS: Results with shield data
    LS->>Files: Store reports

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Remote Garak Scan (Kubeflow Pipelines)
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run (remote)<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    LS->>KFP: Submit pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/443 Bearer Token
    KFP->>LS: validate_inputs<br/>8321/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    LS-->>KFP: Validation result
    KFP->>vLLM: garak_scan probes<br/>HTTP/HTTPS API Token
    vLLM-->>KFP: Model responses
    KFP->>Files: Store scan reports<br/>8321/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    KFP->>S3: Upload result mapping<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/eval/jobs/status<br/>8321/TCP
    LS->>S3: Fetch result mapping<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    S3-->>LS: Result mapping JSON
    LS-->>Client: Job status + results
